{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My son, don’t forget my teaching, but let your heart keep my commandments,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "for they will add to you length of days, years of life, and peace."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Don’t let kindness and truth forsake you. Bind them around your neck."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Write them on the tablet of your heart."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "So you will find favor, and good understanding in the sight of God and man."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Trust in Yahweh with all your heart, and don’t lean on your own understanding."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "In all your ways acknowledge him, and he will make your paths straight."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Don’t be wise in your own eyes. Fear Yahweh, and depart from evil."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It will be health to your body, and nourishment to your bones."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Honor Yahweh with your substance, with the first fruits of all your increase;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "so your barns will be filled with plenty, and your vats will overflow with new wine."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My son, don’t despise Yahweh’s discipline, neither be weary of his correction;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "for whom Yahweh loves, he corrects, even as a father reproves the son in whom he delights."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Happy is the man who finds wisdom, the man who gets understanding."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For her good profit is better than getting silver, and her return is better than fine gold."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She is more precious than rubies. None of the things you can desire are to be compared to her."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Length of days is in her right hand. In her left hand are riches and honor."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Her ways are ways of pleasantness. All her paths are peace."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She is a tree of life to those who lay hold of her. Happy is everyone who retains her."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "By wisdom Yahweh founded the earth. By understanding, he established the heavens."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "By his knowledge, the depths were broken up, and the skies drop down the dew."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My son, let them not depart from your eyes. Keep sound wisdom and discretion,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "so they will be life to your soul, and grace for your neck."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then you shall walk in your way securely. Your foot won’t stumble."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When you lie down, you will not be afraid. Yes, you will lie down, and your sleep will be sweet."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Don’t be afraid of sudden fear, neither of the desolation of the wicked, when it comes;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "for Yahweh will be your confidence, and will keep your foot from being taken."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Don’t withhold good from those to whom it is due, when it is in the power of your hand to do it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Don’t say to your neighbor, "
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Go, and come again; tomorrow I will give it to you,",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "when you have it by you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Don’t devise evil against your neighbor, since he dwells securely by you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Don’t strive with a man without cause, if he has done you no harm."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Don’t envy the man of violence. Choose none of his ways."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "32",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For the perverse is an abomination to Yahweh, but his friendship is with the upright."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "33",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Yahweh’s curse is in the house of the wicked, but he blesses the habitation of the righteous."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "34",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Surely he mocks the mockers, but he gives grace to the humble."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "35",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The wise will inherit glory, but shame will be the promotion of fools."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}